      <h1 class="kestrel-page__title" style="font-size:36px;">The science of density.</h1>
      <div class="kestrel-page__body" style="margin-bottom:48px;">
        <p>The conversation around hair loss has been wrong for decades. The follicle is not a passive victim of genetics — it is an active organ, responsive to its environment, its blood supply, and the signaling molecules that surround it.</p>
        <p>Most men notice thinning not because their hair has stopped growing, but because the growth cycle has shortened. Each follicle spends less time in the growth phase and more time resting. The result is hair that is shorter, finer, and less pigmented.</p>
        <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:20px;font-weight:500;text-transform:uppercase;margin:32px 0 16px;">What the follicle actually needs</h2>
        <p>The follicle requires three things: adequate blood flow, the right signaling molecules, and protection from chronic inflammation. Most hair products address none of these.</p>
        <p>Biomimetic peptides can extend the growth phase and increase the diameter of each hair shaft. Rosemary extract improves microcirculation. Saw palmetto modulates DHT sensitivity without the side effects of pharmaceutical inhibitors.</p>
